# Backend Agent -- MeetingBox Services

## Domain
You own all backend Python microservices under `services/`. There are 5 services:
- `services/web/` -- FastAPI backend (port 8000), WebSocket relay, REST API
- `services/audio/` -- PyAudio capture + webrtcvad segmentation
- `services/transcription/` -- Whisper.cpp transcription, SRT parsing
- `services/ai/` -- Claude (Anthropic) summarization
- `services/ollama/` -- Local LLM container (Dockerfile + entrypoint)

## Architecture
- Services communicate via **Redis pub/sub** on channels `events` and `audio_segments`
- Shared **SQLite** database at `/data/transcripts/meetings.db`
- Tables: `meetings`, `segments`, `summaries`, `local_summaries`
- The web service is the API gateway -- frontend and device-ui talk only to it
- Audio/transcription/AI services are event-driven pipeline workers

## Key Files
- `services/web/main.py` -- FastAPI app, WebSocket, Redis relay
- `services/web/routes/meetings.py` -- Meeting CRUD, recording control, summarization
- `services/web/routes/system.py` -- System status
- `services/web/routes/device.py` -- Device settings, WiFi, integrations
- `services/web/database.py` -- Canonical DB schema (has all tables)
- `services/audio/audio_capture.py` -- Main audio service
- `services/audio/config.yaml` -- Audio/VAD settings
- `services/transcription/transcription_service.py` -- Whisper runner
- `services/ai/ai_service.py` -- Claude integration

## Coding Standards
- Use Python `logging` module instead of `print()` for all output
- Use `with` context managers for SQLite connections and file handles
- Always enable `PRAGMA foreign_keys = ON` after connecting to SQLite
- Use `os.environ.get()` with defaults for all configuration values
- Add type hints to all function signatures
- Wrap multi-step DB operations in transactions
- Handle Redis connection failures with retry logic
- Validate all user input before passing to subprocess or SQL
- Return consistent error response format: `{"detail": "message", "error_code": "CODE"}`
